    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a01-ema-md02\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Step 1 — Run JUSTICE with default parameters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Before exploring uncertainty, confirm the model runs with its default settings. Run the cell before anything else, it loads all required packages and defines shared name lists used throughout the notebook.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Task 1.1** —  the `justice_model` function below does the following:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Hard-reset JUSTICE and instantiate a fresh model with the given `ecs_ensemble` index.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Set `rho` on `model.welfare_function.pure_rate_of_social_time_preference`.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Set `eta` on `model.welfare_function.elasticity_of_marginal_utility_of_consumption`.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Scale the three active damage coefficients (`coefficient_a`, `coefficient_b`, `damage_gdp_ratio_with_gradient`) by `delta`.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. Run with zero abatement (`ECR = 0`) and return all four outcomes as a dict.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"> **Note:** Default argument values are required by the EMA Workbench function model interface.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Task 1.2** — Run the default case (`ecs_ensemble=1`, all other parameters at their defaults) and record the four outcome values.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a01ans-c00\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"execution\": {\n",
    "     \"iopub.execute_input\": \"2026-04-02T09:51:17.066911Z\",\n",
    "     \"iopub.status.busy\": \"2026-04-02T09:51:17.066838Z\",\n",
    "     \"iopub.status.idle\": \"2026-04-02T09:51:19.075605Z\",\n",
