    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Step 2 — Define uncertain parameters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Task 2.1** — Complete the cell below by:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Creating a `Model` object wrapping `justice_model`.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Assigning `uncertainties` — four `RealParameter` objects matching the table in the Background.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Assigning `outcomes` — four `ScalarOutcome` objects.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Task 2.2** — Explain in 2–3 sentences why a *higher* pure rate of time preference `ρ` tends to lead to *less* stringent near-term mitigation. Reference the Ramsey rule in your answer.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"*(Write your answer here)*\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Task 2.3** — Explain why `ecs_ensemble` is a *physical* uncertainty while `ρ`, `η`, `δ` are *normative* uncertainties. What does this distinction imply about which outcomes each type of uncertainty can influence?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"*(Write your answer here)*\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a01ans-c02\",\n",
