    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"em_model = Model('JUSTICE', function=justice_model)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"em_model.uncertainties = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"#YOUR CODE HERE\\n\",\n",
    "    \"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Policy lever: emission control rate applied uniformly across all timesteps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"em_model.levers = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"#YOUR CODE HERE\\n\",\n",
    "    \"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"em_model.outcomes = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"#YOUR CODE HERE\\n\",\n",
    "    \"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Uncertainties : {[u.name for u in em_model.uncertainties]}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Levers        : {[l.name for l in em_model.levers]}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Outcomes      : {[o.name for o in em_model.outcomes]}\\\")\\n\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a01-ema-md04\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Step 3 — Latin Hypercube Sampling ensemble\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Latin Hypercube Sampling (LHS)** divides each uncertain dimension into equally\\n\",\n",
    "    \"probable intervals and samples exactly once from each interval. Compared to Monte Carlo,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"it guarantees better coverage of the full parameter space with fewer samples.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"You first need to define two policies to compare: one with no abatement (ecr_plateau=0.0) and one with moderate abatement (ecr_plateau=0.4). Use Sample to give each policy a name.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"`perform_experiments` uses LHS by default. A single call handles sampling, execution, and result collection.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Task 3.1** — Run 100 scenarios using `SequentialEvaluator`. Store the results as:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `experiments` — a DataFrame with one row per scenario and one column per parameter\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `outcomes` — a dict mapping outcome names to arrays\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
